01:43.271 --> 01:44.772
<i>Okey-doke.</i>

01:44.856 --> 01:46.691
<i>What kind of cheese filling
you want in that?</i>

01:49.819 --> 01:50.820
(SLURPING)

01:51.362 --> 01:55.158
Oh, God.
Fruit is spelled F-R-O-O-T.

01:55.450 --> 01:57.785
And it's got
quotation marks around it.

01:58.369 --> 01:59.370
Hmm...

01:59.912 --> 02:02.915
There's nothing wrong with a little
fast food once or twice a meal.

02:02.999 --> 02:04.375
(WHEEZING)

02:04.459 --> 02:06.878
(GROANING) Heart attack.

02:07.587 --> 02:08.588
(GASPING)

02:10.965 --> 02:11.966
(GULPS)

02:12.133 --> 02:13.384
I'm fine.

02:14.010 --> 02:15.011
(CRACKING)

02:15.094 --> 02:18.389
Ow! I got a bone
in my fruit! That's it.

02:18.681 --> 02:20.391
From now on,
we're not eating anything

02:20.475 --> 02:22.935
unless we know what it is
and where it's from.

02:23.061 --> 02:25.355
We're going to
the local farmers market.

02:25.438 --> 02:27.732
Ah, Mom,
do we have to?

02:41.788 --> 02:43.414
(CLUCKING)

02:46.876 --> 02:48.670
This is what
I'm talking about.

02:48.920 --> 02:52.507
See all the dirt and earwigs?
That's the sign of healthy food.

02:52.757 --> 02:55.426
You think that's healthy,
try this.

02:55.510 --> 02:58.471
I found it growing
at the bottom of my hamper.

03:00.723 --> 03:01.724
Mmm!

03:01.808 --> 03:03.351
So fresh and musty.

03:03.434 --> 03:04.769
