16:12.181 --> 16:15.476
Guess I'll pass the time
by lighting up an El Jerko.

16:22.107 --> 16:23.108
(BIRD CHIRPING)

16:24.776 --> 16:25.819
(COUGHING)

16:25.903 --> 16:28.405
Okay, that's it.
I need some air.

16:33.535 --> 16:34.536
(CRACKLING)

16:35.245 --> 16:36.663
Who's there?

16:37.915 --> 16:40.876
Hermes, is this one of
your zany practical jokes?

16:42.419 --> 16:43.420
(YELLING)

16:50.677 --> 16:51.678
(GASPING)

16:53.388 --> 16:56.350
Leela, are you okay? Did you
drink too many aquaria?

16:56.975 --> 16:58.644
Look, the bone vampire!

17:02.105 --> 17:03.190
(MOANS)

17:03.273 --> 17:06.401
Mr. Peppy attacked me.
Quick, count my bones.

17:06.609 --> 17:08.111
There should be 205.

17:13.951 --> 17:16.036
Okay, that's better.

17:16.118 --> 17:17.204
Keep them coming!

17:17.538 --> 17:21.791
I'm sorry, Fry, but no
vegetarian could have done this.

17:22.084 --> 17:26.505
I know, and as much as I love Mr.
Peppy, I love Leela more.

17:26.964 --> 17:29.132
He has to be
put down.

17:29.466 --> 17:33.845
Ah, don't feel bad. Major Mac:Zongo
is an experienced hunter.

17:33.929 --> 17:37.140
He'll blow Mr. Peppy's head off
as painlessly as possible.

17:37.307 --> 17:38.892
No, not MacZongo!

17:38.976 --> 17:42.771
If anyone is going to kill Mr.
Peppy, it should be me.

17:42.854 --> 17:45.482
Fry, I know
you're upset right now,

17:45.566 --> 17:49.653
but I hope you'll consider donating
the body to science dinner.

17:49.736 --> 17:50.737
(SLURPING)

17:54.366 --> 17:55.659
Here, Ivlr- Peppy-

17:55.826 --> 17:58.161
Mmm, lovely bones.

17:58.453 --> 18:01.665
We've been walking for hours. I
hope we can find our way back.

18:01.873 --> 18:04.418
Don't worry, I left a
trail of bread crumbs.

18:04.543 --> 18:06.753
And I left a trail of cigars.

18:10.465 --> 18:12.259
You don't have
to do this, Fry.

18:12.342 --> 18:14.803
Mr. Peppy just gave me
a little love concussion.

18:14.886 --> 18:16.972
Thanks, Leela,
but I have no choice.

18:17.055 --> 18:20.350
Icanfilet my monstrous de-boner
get anywhere near you.

18:20.434 --> 18:21.852
There it is!

18:23.937 --> 18:25.355
Well, this is it.

18:25.647 --> 18:27.482
You guys wait here.

18:27.566 --> 18:30.736
This is going to kill him
more than it does me.

18:33.280 --> 18:34.531
Goodbye, boy.

18:34.615 --> 18:37.659
I'll think of you whenever
I sit on something round.

18:40.996 --> 18:41.997
(SCREAMS)

18:43.874 --> 18:44.875
<i>(EVERY ONE GASP S)</i>

18:44.958 --> 18:47.044
What's happening?
Did you kill it?

18:47.294 --> 18:51.131
The bloody idiot bloody shot me.
I'm all bloody bloody!

18:51.381 --> 18:52.883
(EXCLAIMING)

18:52.966 --> 18:55.427
Mr. Peppy,
bullets make you talk?

18:55.719 --> 18:57.596
That's not Mr. Peppy.

19:00.057 --> 19:02.434
Jinkies, he Scooby-Doo-ed us.

19:02.684 --> 19:05.062
Why, Major MacZongo, why?

19:05.270 --> 19:09.316
It's been 3O years since last
I killed a bone vampire.

19:09.399 --> 19:11.985
The villagers didn't idolize
me like they used to.

19:12.194 --> 19:14.279
You seemed pretty
popular at the pub.

19:14.446 --> 19:16.907
I work there as a greeter.

19:16.990 --> 19:19.326
Your beast was my chance
to be a hero again,

19:19.409 --> 19:21.203
but the damn thing
was a vegetarian,

19:21.328 --> 19:23.163
so I slaughtered
the sheep myself.

19:23.413 --> 19:24.915
But why did you attack me?

19:25.123 --> 19:28.251
So I could impress you by seeking
revenge on the creature.

19:28.377 --> 19:30.587
Us greeters don't
get a lot of action.

19:30.671 --> 19:32.756
On paper it seemed like
a win-win situation.

19:32.964 --> 19:35.592
Do you realize
what this means, Fry?

19:35.717 --> 19:38.345
Your pet's not
dangerous after all.

19:38.428 --> 19:41.640
I told you. Mr. Peppy's
a lover, not a fighter,

19:41.723 --> 19:44.184
like Dwayne "The Rock"
"The Tooth Fairy" Johnson.

19:44.601 --> 19:46.436
(CHEERING)

19:47.354 --> 19:48.772
(SLURPING SOUND)

19:48.855 --> 19:51.191
Hey, what's that
bone-sucking sound?

19:54.444 --> 19:56.988
It's Mr. Peppy.
I'd know him anywhere.

19:57.280 --> 20:00.367
Huh. So apparently, Major
Mac:Zongo and Mr. Peppy

20:00.450 --> 20:02.285
were each doing abouthafi
the sheep-killing.

20:03.120 --> 20:04.121
(GROWLING)

20:04.454 --> 20:05.455
(SCREAMING)

20:08.125 --> 20:12.170
Why, Mr. Peppy, why? That tickles.
(LAUGHING)

20:12.254 --> 20:15.465
(CRYING) Now I really
do have to kill you.

20:17.467 --> 20:19.010
Wait! Don't shoot!

20:19.302 --> 20:21.096
The beast
is a Godsend.

20:21.179 --> 20:24.558
Like I said, we've more livestock
than we can slaughter,

20:24.641 --> 20:28.645
but thanks to this ravenous
bogle, that's no more a problem.

20:28.937 --> 20:30.230
Angus is right.

20:30.313 --> 20:32.566
The cursed thing
even debones them,

20:32.649 --> 20:36.069
which is perfect for today's
fast-paced, lazy consumer.

20:36.319 --> 20:39.156
(SPEAKING IN
INDECIPHERABLE LANGUAGE)

20:39.322 --> 20:40.866
The beast must live!

20:41.241 --> 20:43.118
(CHEERING)

20:44.077 --> 20:45.787
You know what
the best part is?

20:45.871 --> 20:49.624
From now on, whenever we're
eating fresh, organic space-meat,

20:49.708 --> 20:51.960
we'll know exactly
where it comes from.

20:53.503 --> 20:57.466
One bucket of double-fried, triple-salted,
boneless sheep tots, please.

20:57.632 --> 20:59.301
<i>What kind of cheese filling
you want in that?</i>

20:59.634 --> 21:01.261
All kinds.

21:01.344 --> 21:02.846
Ah... Make it two,

21:03.513 --> 21:06.057
<i>and a small whiskey.
Large.</i>

21:37.005 --> 21:38.006
English - US - PSDH
